Load Balancer : helps in distributing traffic to multiple instances of servers. preventing a server from overloaded.
    1.Server side: centralized load balancer.
    2.Client side: Load balancing capability present inside the client or it uses a library to take decisions.

1.with RestTemplate:
    1.add dependency -> spring-cloud-starter-loadbalancer.
    2.use @LoadBalanced: -> spring intercepts the requests and call service discovery and do load balancing.

